1. Project Leadership Development Plan (Diplomatic and Enhanced Revision)

Development Goal:

	•	Develop leadership skills by guiding the technical execution of data science projects, contributing to project outcomes, and supporting the team through technical challenges and solution design.

Success Measures:

	•	Lead specific technical aspects of at least two significant data science projects, contributing to successful project outcomes.
	•	Collaborate with business stakeholders and the team to create data science questions from initial ideas and design methodologies to solve them.
	•	Break down larger projects into smaller, manageable tasks, ensuring alignment with business goals and timelines.
	•	Provide guidance to the team in addressing complex technical challenges and design innovative solutions.
	•	Receive positive feedback from the manager, stakeholders, and team members on leadership and technical problem-solving.

Skill Development:

	•	Guide the technical components of projects, contributing to the design and execution of effective data science solutions.
	•	Enhance decision-making abilities by working closely with both the business stakeholders and the technical team to align project goals with business objectives.

Competency Development:

	•	Strategic thinking in creating actionable data science questions from business challenges and designing methodologies to address them.
	•	Effective communication of technical progress, ensuring both business and technical stakeholders are aligned throughout the project.

Development Timeframe:

	•	Over the next 6-12 months.

Action Plan:

	•	Collaborate with business stakeholders to translate their needs into data science questions and design methodologies to address them.
	•	Break down complex projects into smaller tasks, coordinating with team members to ensure the technical aspects align with broader business goals.
	•	Provide support to the team in overcoming technical challenges by offering guidance on solution design and methods.
	•	Regularly communicate technical progress to the manager and stakeholders, ensuring alignment with both project goals and business strategy.
	•	Seek regular feedback from the manager, team members, and business stakeholders on leadership effectiveness and decision-making in technical areas.

Potential Barriers:

	•	Managing complex technical challenges while ensuring alignment with broader project goals and business objectives.
	• careful coordination within the team.

Support or Resources Needed:

	•	Manager’s feedback on leadership and decision-making in technical areas.
	•	Opportunities to collaborate closely with business stakeholders to shape project goals and methodologies.
	•	Guidance from the manager on balancing technical leadership with team collaboration and project execution.

2. Business Acumen & Strategic Alignment Development Plan

Development Goal:

	•	Enhance understanding of business goals and align data science efforts to support strategic objectives, while improving knowledge of KPIs in the insurance and finance sectors.

Success Measures:

	•	Contribute to strategic decision-making through data-driven insights.
	•	Participate in business meetings and provide input on how data science can solve business challenges.
	•	Expand understanding of key business performance metrics and their relevance to data science work.

Skill Development:

	•	Business acumen related to insurance and finance.
	•	Strategic alignment of data science with business goals.
	•	Understanding KPIs and how they drive strategic decisions in the insurance industry.

Competency Development:

	•	Business communication and ability to translate technical outcomes into business value.
	•	Strategic thinking focused on maximizing data science’s impact on business objectives.

Development Timeframe:

	•	Over the next 6-12 months.

Action Plan:

	•	Attend key business meetings to better understand company objectives and how data science projects can align with those goals.
	•	Work closely with business stakeholders to define data science projects that align with business priorities.
	•	Take training in business strategy or insurance-related topics to deepen business acumen.
	•	Continue to enhance understanding of business KPIs to provide more impactful data science solutions.

Potential Barriers:

	•	Limited exposure to higher-level business meetings or strategic decision-making discussions.
	•	Time constraints while balancing technical work with business learning.

Support or Resources Needed:

	•	Opportunities from the manager to attend more business-focused meetings and discussions.
	•	Access to business strategy or insurance industry training.

3. Mentorship & Team Leadership Development Plan

Development Goal:

	•	Develop mentorship and team leadership skills by guiding junior team members and contributing to team collaboration.

Success Measures:

	•	Act as a mentor for junior data scientists and provide guidance on technical and project work.
	•	Receive feedback from mentees and management on leadership effectiveness.
	•	Contribute to the knowledge base by instructing team members and helping them grow technically.

Skill Development:

	•	Mentoring junior team members in both technical skills and career development.
	•	Team leadership in collaborative projects.

Competency Development:

	•	Coaching and providing constructive feedback.
	•	Developing leadership skills in a non-managerial role.

Development Timeframe:

	•	Over the next 6 months.

Action Plan:

	•	Take responsibility for mentoring at least one junior team member.
	•	Offer guidance during team meetings and share best practices.
	•	Participate in internal leadership training focused on coaching and mentorship.
	•	Contribute to the knowledge base by organizing technical learning sessions or documentation to support team growth.

Potential Barriers:

	•	Balancing mentorship responsibilities with individual project work.
	•	Ensuring adequate time to provide thorough guidance to mentees.

Support or Resources Needed:

	•	Encouragement and guidance from the manager to take on mentorship opportunities.
	•	Time allocated to develop structured mentoring sessions or materials.

4. Communication & Stakeholder Management Development Plan

Development Goal:

	•	Strengthen communication skills, especially in translating complex technical work into clear, actionable insights for non-technical stakeholders.

Success Measures:

	•	Effectively communicate project outcomes and technical concepts to business stakeholders, resulting in actionable decisions.
	•	Receive positive feedback from stakeholders on the clarity of communication.

Skill Development:

	•	Business communication and stakeholder management.
	•	Simplifying complex technical findings for broader audiences.

Competency Development:

	•	Influence and negotiation in cross-functional teams.
	•	Ability to present data science work in business terms.

Development Timeframe:

	•	Over the next 6 months.

Action Plan:

	•	Present key findings to stakeholders and leadership in regular project updates.
	•	Take part in communication training focused on delivering technical concepts to non-technical audiences.
	•	Seek feedback on communication style and effectiveness after meetings or presentations.

Potential Barriers:

	•	Ensuring technical concepts are sufficiently simplified without losing accuracy.
	•	Limited opportunities for regular presentations to stakeholders.

Support or Resources Needed:

	•	Opportunities to present technical work at business meetings or stakeholder gatherings.
	•	Manager’s feedback on communication style and how to enhance clarity.

5. Cross-Team Collaboration & External Engagement Development Plan

Development Goal:

	•	Build collaboration with other teams and managers to identify shared opportunities, and participate in technical or business-oriented events to enhance knowledge sharing and technical communication.

Success Measures:

	•	Successfully initiate at least two collaborative projects or shared initiatives with other teams.
	•	Actively participate in relevant conferences or technical-business events, and share the insights or outcomes with the team.
	•	Provide clear and actionable communication of results to other teams or stakeholders when requested.

Skill Development:

	•	Cross-functional collaboration and identification of shared opportunities for team and project synergies.
	•	Technical communication and engagement with external or industry stakeholders.

Competency Development:

	•	Networking and building relationships across teams and departments.
	•	Representing your team in external conferences or technical events to identify industry trends and best practices.

Development Timeframe:

	•	Over the next 6-12 months.

Action Plan:

	•	Identify and initiate collaborative projects with other teams (e.g., engineering, business analytics, or operations).
	•	Attend at least two technical or business-oriented conferences or industry events in the next 12 months.
	•	Participate in company’s French courses to improve networking opportunities with French-speaking colleagues.
	•	Share the outcomes of external events and how they can benefit internal projects with the broader team.
	•	Communicate results and insights with other teams or stakeholders when asked, ensuring that information is shared efficiently.

Potential Barriers:

	•	Limited time to attend external events while managing ongoing projects.
	•	Ensuring cross-team collaboration aligns with current project timelines and goals.

Support or Resources Needed:

	•	Manager’s support in identifying relevant conferences or external events to attend.
	•	Guidance on initiating cross-team collaborations that align with strategic goals.